  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Acts 8:12-13",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 8:12-13",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But when they believed Philip, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. When they became spectators of Philip’s miracles, and were convinced that they were real, and those of Simon a mere sham; or, when they believed the doctrine that Philip preached, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "concerning the kingdom of God, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they then saw and felt the real power of God, and submitted thereto; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and were baptized, both men and women ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Thus making an open profession of their faith in the gospel. By the influence of divine grace, working with the word, they that had been led captive by Satan, were brought into obedience to Christ. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then Simon himself believed — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The truth of the doctrine taught by this messenger of God, though his heart was not truly changed by its power: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and when he was baptized ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— On a profession of that faith; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he continued with Philip — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Courting a further acquaintance with him; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and wondered, beholding the miracles, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Greek, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was astonished, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or filled with amazement, as the Samaritans had formerly been, at the sight of his magical performances. “It is with peculiar elegance and propriety, that the same word which had been used to express the manner in which the Samaritans were affected with Simon’s enchantments, is here used to describe the impression which Philip’s miracles made on him.” Thus Doddridge; who adds, “We see in this, as in a thousand nearer instances, that there may be a speculative faith in the gospel where there is no true piety; and if such persons, on the profession of that faith, where nothing appears contrary to it, be admitted to those ordinances by which Christians are distinguished from the rest of mankind, it is an evil in the present state of things unavoidable, and the conduct of Christian ministers and societies, in admitting such, will be less displeasing to God than a rigorous severity.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
